\subsection{Components of a Sato-Tate group}
\begin{definition}\label{st_group.components}
\uses{st_group.component_group,st_group.connected,st_group.definition,st_group.identity_component}
As a compact Lie group, a {{KNOWL('st_group.definition', 'Sato-Tate group')}} $G$ need not be {{KNOWL('st_group.connected', 'connected')}}, but it necessarily consists of a finite set of components, each of which is a coset of the {{KNOWL('st_group.identity_component', "identity component")}} $G^0$, a normal subgroup.  The number of components is equal to the cardinality of the {{KNOWL('st_group.component_group', "component group")}} $G/G^0$.
\end{definition}


